Cote Flatiron NYCso my review is based on the fact that this is a michelin star restaurant nothing was necessarily bad but i obviously had high expectations going in i really wanted to like this place but it was disappointing idk if its because our reservation was late at night pm but the service was so weird we were seated minutes late as all the reviews had warned and when i ordered an XL wine i also loooved the variety of side dishes and they were all really good the meat was yummy but it didnt blow my mind the servers cook your meat for you but some of them not very well ive definitely had better meat at a better price one thing that did bother me and this might be the asian in me but i wasnt a fan of the servers sprinkling salt on the meat with long painted fingernails maybe im just being nitpicky at this point but i thought michelin star restaurants put more thought into this kind of stuff tldr was not worth my butchers cut for wedge salad on the house steak tartare kimchi Cote Flatiron NYCso my review is based on the fact that this is a michelin star restaurant nothing was necessarily bad but i obviously had high expectations going in i really wanted to like this place but it was disappointing idk if its because our reservation was late at night pm but the service was so weird we were seated minutes late as all the reviews had warned and when i ordered an XL wine they gave me a small one while they did give me more it just made me a bit less enthusiastic about the experience from the start as for the food the appetizers steak tartare wedge salad were delicious i also loooved the variety of side dishes and they were all really good the meat was yummy but it didnt blow my mind the servers cook your meat for you but some of them not very well ive definitely had better meat at a better price one thing that did bother me and this might be the asian in me but i wasnt a fan of the servers sprinkling salt on the meat with long painted fingernails maybe im just being nitpicky at this point but i thought michelin star restaurants put more thought into this kind of stuff tldr was not worth my butchers cut for wedge salad on the house steak tartare kimchi
